article.headline: Portland State 35, McNeese State 14
article.story:
PORTLAND, Ore. (AP) -- Allen Kennett and Joe Rubin ran for two
touchdowns each as Portland State upset McNeese State 35-14 on
Saturday.

Kennett and Rubin normally rarely carry the ball for the Vikings
(2-1), but the team's top rusher -- Ryan Fuqua -- left the game
early in the second half with a bruised hip and Kennett and Rubin
picked up the slack.

The game was dominated by opportunistic defenses and a slew of
first-half penalties. McNeese State (2-2), ranked No. 12 in
Division I-AA coming in, had 320 yards in total offense, but the
Cowboys were penalized 13 times for 122 yards and they turned the
ball over five times.

Trailing 21-7, the Cowboys' hopes for a comeback were dashed
when Portland State linebacker Ryan Friesen intercepted a pass and
returned it to the McNeese State 1. Two plays later, Kennett scored
to give the Vikings a 28-7 lead.

McNeese State then fumbled the ensuing kickoff and Rubin scored
from 18 yards out on the next play to make it 35-7.

McNeese State answered with a length-of-the-field drive, which
ended with Kris Bush's three-yard touchdown run with 18 seconds
left in the game. It was the Cowboys' only offensive score of the
game.

The first half saw a combined 20 penalties for 179 yards. One
Portland State series in the second quarter contained seven
penalties, including five against the Vikings. Portland State still
managed to drive the ball to the McNeese State 34 before having to
punt.

Mistakes also played a key role in two of the three touchdowns
that were scored in the first half.

Fuqua got the Vikings on the board first with a four-yard
scoring run midway through the first quarter that was set up by
Chris Berg's interception deep in McNeese State territory.

The Cowboys gave the ball right back after a three-and-out
possession and Portland State scored five plays later on a six-yard
run by Kennett.

The Cowboys got their first score late in the first quarter when
Stephen Barrett scooped up a fumble and ran 15 yards to trim the
Vikings' lead to 14-7.

Fuqua ran for 122 yards and has 4,036 rushing yards for his
career. Rubin and Kennett added 60 and 43 yards, respectively. The
Vikings finished with 325 yards of total offense but they were
penalized 17 times for 157 yards.

Scott Pendarvis completed 15 of 32 passes for 170 yards to lead
the Cowboys. Henry Smith had eight receptions for 101 yards.
